s668: Two. Tian Rong's younger brother Heng rebelled at Chengyang, attacked Jia, fled to Chu; Chu killed Jia.
s678: Fourteen. Surrendered to Han, Ang deposed.
s683: Three. Xiang Yu with troops of thirty thousand broke Han troops of five hundred sixty thousand.
s689: Qi King Tian Guang began. Guang was Rong's son; Heng established him.
s692: Fourth month. King attacked Chu to Pengcheng, defeated and fled.
s698: Thirty-three. Followed Han to attack Chu.
s700: Six. Followed Han to attack Chu.
s713: Fifth month. King fled to Xingyang.
s719: Thirty-four. Bao returned, rebelled against Han.
